{
  "video_id": "Mlt6kaNjoeI",
  "title": "Alastair Parvin: Architecture for the people by the people",
  "es": 1,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 7000.0,
      "text": "Translator: Joseph Geni Reviewer: Morton Bast"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 12884.0,
      "end_time": 16530.0,
      "text": "When we use the word \"architect\" or \"designer,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 16530.0,
      "end_time": 18852.0,
      "text": "what we usually mean is a professional,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 18852.0,
      "end_time": 21324.0,
      "text": "someone who gets paid,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 21324.0,
      "end_time": 24247.0,
      "text": "and we tend to assume that it&#39;s those professionals"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 24247.0,
      "end_time": 26228.0,
      "text": "who are going to be the ones to help us solve"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 26228.0,
      "end_time": 28788.0,
      "text": "the really big, systemic design challenges that we face"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 28788.0,
      "end_time": 32633.0,
      "text": "like climate change, urbanization and social inequality."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 32633.000000000004,
      "end_time": 35717.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s our kind of working presumption."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 35717.0,
      "end_time": 38724.0,
      "text": "And I think it&#39;s wrong, actually."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 38724.0,
      "end_time": 41971.0,
      "text": "In 2008, I was just about to graduate from architecture school"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 41972.0,
      "end_time": 44645.0,
      "text": "after several years, and go out and get a job,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 44645.0,
      "end_time": 47570.0,
      "text": "and this happened."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 47570.0,
      "end_time": 49820.0,
      "text": "The economy ran out of jobs."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 49820.0,
      "end_time": 52275.0,
      "text": "And a couple of things struck me about this."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 52275.0,
      "end_time": 56400.0,
      "text": "One, don&#39;t listen to career advisers."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 56500.0,
      "end_time": 60661.0,
      "text": "And two, actually this is a fascinating paradox for architecture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 60661.0,
      "end_time": 64931.0,
      "text": "which is that, as a society, we&#39;ve never needed design thinking more,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 64931.0,
      "end_time": 68889.0,
      "text": "and yet architecture was literally becoming unemployed."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 68889.0,
      "end_time": 72440.0,
      "text": "It strikes me that we talk very deeply about design,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 72440.0,
      "end_time": 74556.0,
      "text": "but actually there&#39;s an economics behind architecture"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 74556.0,
      "end_time": 77240.0,
      "text": "that we don&#39;t talk about, and I think we need to."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 77240.0,
      "end_time": 80655.0,
      "text": "And a good place to start is your own paycheck."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 80655.0,
      "end_time": 83970.0,
      "text": "So, as a bottom-of-the-rung architecture graduate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 83970.0,
      "end_time": 86730.0,
      "text": "I might expect to earn about 24,000 pounds."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 86730.0,
      "end_time": 89689.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s about 36,000, 37,000 dollars."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 89689.0,
      "end_time": 91393.0,
      "text": "Now in terms of the whole world&#39;s population,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 91394.0,
      "end_time": 96276.0,
      "text": "that already puts me in the top 1.95 richest people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 96276.0,
      "end_time": 100360.0,
      "text": "which raises the question of, who is it I&#39;m working for?"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 100360.0,
      "end_time": 102747.0,
      "text": "The uncomfortable fact is that"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 102747.0,
      "end_time": 105631.0,
      "text": "actually almost everything that we call architecture today"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 105631.0,
      "end_time": 107923.0,
      "text": "is actually the business of designing"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 107923.0,
      "end_time": 110848.0,
      "text": "for about the richest one percent of the world&#39;s population,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 110848.0,
      "end_time": 113770.0,
      "text": "and it always has been."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 113770.0,
      "end_time": 114824.0,
      "text": "The reason why we forgot that"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 114824.0,
      "end_time": 116926.0,
      "text": "is because the times in history when architecture"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 116927.0,
      "end_time": 119852.0,
      "text": "did the most to transform society were those times"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 119852.0,
      "end_time": 122509.0,
      "text": "when, actually, the one percent would build"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 122509.0,
      "end_time": 125544.0,
      "text": "on behalf of the 99 percent, for various different reasons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 125544.0,
      "end_time": 128158.0,
      "text": "whether that was through philanthropy in the 19th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 128157.99999999999,
      "end_time": 130428.99999999999,
      "text": "communism in the early 20th,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 130429.0,
      "end_time": 133467.0,
      "text": "the welfare state, and most recently, of course,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 133467.0,
      "end_time": 137830.0,
      "text": "through this inflated real estate bubble."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 137830.0,
      "end_time": 140391.0,
      "text": "And all of those booms, in their own various ways,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 140391.0,
      "end_time": 142310.0,
      "text": "have now kicked the bucket,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 142310.0,
      "end_time": 144596.0,
      "text": "and we&#39;re back in this situation"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 144596.0,
      "end_time": 149512.0,
      "text": "where the smartest designers and architects in the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 149512.0,
      "end_time": 153292.0,
      "text": "are only really able to work for one percent of the population."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 153292.0,
      "end_time": 155402.0,
      "text": "Now it&#39;s not just that that&#39;s bad for democracy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 155402.0,
      "end_time": 157241.0,
      "text": "though I think it probably is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 157241.0,
      "end_time": 160337.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s actually not a very clever business strategy, actually."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 160337.0,
      "end_time": 163196.0,
      "text": "I think the challenge facing the next generation of architects"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 163196.0,
      "end_time": 165238.0,
      "text": "is, how are we going to turn our client"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 165238.0,
      "end_time": 168859.0,
      "text": "from the one percent to the 100 percent?"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 168859.0,
      "end_time": 172433.0,
      "text": "And I want to offer three slightly counterintuitive ideas"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 172433.0,
      "end_time": 174275.0,
      "text": "for how it might be done."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 174275.0,
      "end_time": 177657.0,
      "text": "The first is, I think we need to question this idea"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 177657.0,
      "end_time": 179948.0,
      "text": "that architecture is about making buildings."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 179948.0,
      "end_time": 182692.0,
      "text": "Actually, a building is about the most expensive solution"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 182692.0,
      "end_time": 185708.0,
      "text": "you can think of to almost any given problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 185708.0,
      "end_time": 188236.0,
      "text": "And fundamentally, design should be much, much more interested"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 188236.0,
      "end_time": 190968.0,
      "text": "in solving problems and creating new conditions."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 190968.0,
      "end_time": 192489.0,
      "text": "So here&#39;s a story."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 192490.0,
      "end_time": 194880.0,
      "text": "The office was working with a school,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 194880.0,
      "end_time": 196513.0,
      "text": "and they had an old Victorian school building."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 196514.0,
      "end_time": 199245.0,
      "text": "And they said to the architects, \"Look,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 199245.0,
      "end_time": 201198.0,
      "text": "our corridors are an absolute nightmare."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 201198.0,
      "end_time": 203564.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re far too small. They get congested between classes."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 203564.0,
      "end_time": 205947.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s bullying. We can&#39;t control them."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 205947.0,
      "end_time": 208789.0,
      "text": "So what we want you to do is re-plan our entire building,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 208789.0,
      "end_time": 210978.0,
      "text": "and we know it&#39;s going to cost several million pounds,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 210979.0,
      "end_time": 212890.0,
      "text": "but we&#39;re reconciled to the fact.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 212890.0,
      "end_time": 215595.0,
      "text": "And the team thought about this, and they went away,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 215596.0,
      "end_time": 217613.0,
      "text": "and they said, \"Actually, don&#39;t do that."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 217613.0,
      "end_time": 220393.0,
      "text": "Instead, get rid of the school bell."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 220393.0,
      "end_time": 223222.0,
      "text": "And instead of having one school bell that goes off once,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 223222.0,
      "end_time": 225480.0,
      "text": "have several smaller school bells that go off"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 225480.0,
      "end_time": 227727.0,
      "text": "in different places and different times,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 227728.0,
      "end_time": 229976.0,
      "text": "distribute the traffic through the corridors.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 229976.0,
      "end_time": 231393.0,
      "text": "It solves the same problem,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 231393.0,
      "end_time": 234201.0,
      "text": "but instead of spending several million pounds,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 234201.0,
      "end_time": 236344.0,
      "text": "you spend several hundred pounds."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 236344.0,
      "end_time": 239144.0,
      "text": "Now, it looks like you&#39;re doing yourself out of a job,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 239144.0,
      "end_time": 241705.0,
      "text": "but you&#39;re not. You&#39;re actually making yourself more useful."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 241705.0,
      "end_time": 243178.0,
      "text": "Architects are actually really, really good"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 243178.0,
      "end_time": 245520.0,
      "text": "at this kind of resourceful, strategic thinking."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 245520.0,
      "end_time": 247482.0,
      "text": "And the problem is that, like a lot of design professions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 247482.0,
      "end_time": 249665.0,
      "text": "we got fixated on the idea of providing"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 249665.0,
      "end_time": 251946.0,
      "text": "a particular kind of consumer product,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 251946.0,
      "end_time": 254416.0,
      "text": "and I don&#39;t think that needs to be the case anymore."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 254416.0,
      "end_time": 258617.0,
      "text": "The second idea worth questioning is this 20th-century thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 258617.00000000003,
      "end_time": 261878.00000000003,
      "text": "that mass architecture is about big --"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 261878.0,
      "end_time": 264472.0,
      "text": "big buildings and big finance."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 264472.0,
      "end_time": 266561.0,
      "text": "Actually, we&#39;ve got ourselves locked into this"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 266561.0,
      "end_time": 268967.0,
      "text": "Industrial Era mindset which says that"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 268968.0,
      "end_time": 272454.0,
      "text": "the only people who can make cities are large organizations"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 272454.0,
      "end_time": 274972.0,
      "text": "or corporations who build on our behalf,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 274972.0,
      "end_time": 276780.0,
      "text": "procuring whole neighborhoods"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 276780.0,
      "end_time": 280212.0,
      "text": "in single, monolithic projects, and of course,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 280213.0,
      "end_time": 282432.0,
      "text": "form follows finance."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 282432.0,
      "end_time": 285456.0,
      "text": "So what you end up with are single, monolithic neighborhoods"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 285456.0,
      "end_time": 289144.0,
      "text": "based on this kind of one-size-fits-all model."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 289144.0,
      "end_time": 291657.0,
      "text": "And a lot of people can&#39;t even afford them."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 291657.0,
      "end_time": 294623.0,
      "text": "But what if, actually, it&#39;s possible now for cities"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 294624.0,
      "end_time": 297394.0,
      "text": "to be made not just by the few with a lot"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 297394.0,
      "end_time": 300582.0,
      "text": "but also by the many with a bit?"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 300582.0,
      "end_time": 301876.0,
      "text": "And when they do, they bring with them"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 301876.0,
      "end_time": 305215.0,
      "text": "a completely different set of values about the place that they want to live."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 305215.0,
      "end_time": 307318.0,
      "text": "And it raises really interesting questions about,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 307319.0,
      "end_time": 310602.0,
      "text": "how will we plan cities? How will finance development?"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 310602.0,
      "end_time": 312263.0,
      "text": "How will we sell design services?"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 312263.0,
      "end_time": 314503.0,
      "text": "What would it mean for democratic societies"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 314503.0,
      "end_time": 316902.0,
      "text": "to offer their citizens a right to build?"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 316903.0,
      "end_time": 319183.0,
      "text": "And in a way it should be kind of obvious, right,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 319183.0,
      "end_time": 324652.0,
      "text": "that in the 21st century, maybe cities can be developed by citizens."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 324652.0,
      "end_time": 327816.0,
      "text": "And thirdly, we need to remember that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 327816.0,
      "end_time": 330167.0,
      "text": "from a strictly economic point of view,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 330167.0,
      "end_time": 335130.0,
      "text": "design shares a category with sex and care of the elderly --"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 335130.0,
      "end_time": 337609.0,
      "text": "mostly it&#39;s done by amateurs."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 337609.0,
      "end_time": 339495.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s a good thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 339495.0,
      "end_time": 342965.0,
      "text": "Most of the work takes place outside of the monetary economy"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 342965.0,
      "end_time": 345250.0,
      "text": "in what&#39;s called the social economy or the core economy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 345250.0,
      "end_time": 347417.0,
      "text": "which is people doing it for themselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 347417.0,
      "end_time": 350664.0,
      "text": "And the problem is that, up until now,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 350665.0,
      "end_time": 352467.0,
      "text": "it was the monetary economy which had"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 352467.0,
      "end_time": 354625.0,
      "text": "all the infrastructure and all the tools."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 354625.0,
      "end_time": 356448.0,
      "text": "So the challenge we face is, how are we going"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 356448.0,
      "end_time": 359681.0,
      "text": "to build the tools, the infrastructure and the institutions"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 359682.0,
      "end_time": 361422.0,
      "text": "for architecture&#39;s social economy?"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 361422.0,
      "end_time": 364154.0,
      "text": "And that began with open-source software."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 364154.0,
      "end_time": 366522.0,
      "text": "And over the last few years, it&#39;s been moving"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 366522.0,
      "end_time": 369170.0,
      "text": "into the physical world with open-source hardware,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 369170.0,
      "end_time": 370546.0,
      "text": "which are freely shared blueprints"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 370547.0,
      "end_time": 374593.0,
      "text": "that anyone can download and make for themselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 374593.0,
      "end_time": 377834.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s where 3D printing gets really, really interesting."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 377834.0,
      "end_time": 381370.0,
      "text": "Right? When suddenly you had a 3D printer"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 381370.0,
      "end_time": 382924.0,
      "text": "that was open-source, the parts for which"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 382924.0,
      "end_time": 385205.0,
      "text": "could be made on another 3D printer."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 385205.0,
      "end_time": 388265.0,
      "text": "Or the same idea here, which is for a CNC machine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 388266.0,
      "end_time": 392762.0,
      "text": "which is like a large printer that can cut sheets of plywood."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 392762.0,
      "end_time": 395576.0,
      "text": "What these technologies are doing is radically"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 395576.0,
      "end_time": 398657.0,
      "text": "lowering the thresholds of time and cost and skill."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 398657.0,
      "end_time": 400239.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re challenging the idea that"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 400239.0,
      "end_time": 404650.0,
      "text": "if you want something to be affordable it&#39;s got to be one-size-fits-all."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 404650.0,
      "end_time": 406398.0,
      "text": "And they&#39;re distributing massively"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 406398.0,
      "end_time": 409285.0,
      "text": "really complex manufacturing capabilities."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 409285.0,
      "end_time": 413416.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re moving into this future where the factory is everywhere,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 413416.0,
      "end_time": 414611.0,
      "text": "and increasingly that means"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 414611.0,
      "end_time": 417897.0,
      "text": "that the design team is everyone."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 417898.0,
      "end_time": 420424.0,
      "text": "That really is an industrial revolution."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 420424.0,
      "end_time": 423640.0,
      "text": "And when we think that the major ideological conflicts"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 423640.0,
      "end_time": 425657.0,
      "text": "that we inherited were all based around this question"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 425658.0,
      "end_time": 427570.0,
      "text": "of who should control the means of production,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 427570.0,
      "end_time": 430296.0,
      "text": "and these technologies are coming back with a solution:"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 430297.0,
      "end_time": 434286.0,
      "text": "actually, maybe no one. All of us."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 434286.0,
      "end_time": 436455.0,
      "text": "And we were fascinated by"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 436455.0,
      "end_time": 439620.0,
      "text": "what that might mean for architecture."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 439620.0,
      "end_time": 441584.0,
      "text": "So about a year and a half ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 441584.0,
      "end_time": 443480.0,
      "text": "we started working on a project called WikiHouse,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 443480.0,
      "end_time": 446754.0,
      "text": "and WikiHouse is an open-source construction system."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 446754.0,
      "end_time": 449552.0,
      "text": "And the idea is to make it possible for anyone"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 449552.0,
      "end_time": 451936.0,
      "text": "to go online, access a freely shared library"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 451936.0,
      "end_time": 456397.0,
      "text": "of 3D models which they can download and adapt in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 456397.0,
      "end_time": 459788.0,
      "text": "at the moment, SketchUp, because it&#39;s free, and it&#39;s easy to use,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 459788.0,
      "end_time": 462347.0,
      "text": "and almost at the click of a switch"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 462347.0,
      "end_time": 464830.0,
      "text": "they can generate a set of cutting files"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 464831.0,
      "end_time": 466872.0,
      "text": "which allow them, in effect,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 466872.0,
      "end_time": 470600.0,
      "text": "to print out the parts from a house using a CNC machine"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 470600.0,
      "end_time": 473271.0,
      "text": "and a standard sheet material like plywood."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 473271.0,
      "end_time": 476391.0,
      "text": "And the parts are all numbered,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 476391.0,
      "end_time": 480568.0,
      "text": "and basically what you end up with is a really big IKEA kit."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 480568.0,
      "end_time": 482839.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 482839.0,
      "end_time": 485105.0,
      "text": "And it goes together without any bolts."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 485105.0,
      "end_time": 487295.0,
      "text": "It uses wedge and peg connections."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 487295.0,
      "end_time": 489439.0,
      "text": "And even the mallets to make it"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 489439.0,
      "end_time": 491919.0,
      "text": "can be provided on the cutting sheets as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 491919.0,
      "end_time": 494455.0,
      "text": "And a team of about two or three people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 494456.0,
      "end_time": 496495.0,
      "text": "working together, can build this."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 496495.0,
      "end_time": 498975.0,
      "text": "They don&#39;t need any traditional construction skills."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 498975.0,
      "end_time": 502126.0,
      "text": "They don&#39;t need a huge array of power tools or anything like that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 502126.0,
      "end_time": 504638.0,
      "text": "and they can build a small house of about this size"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 504639.0,
      "end_time": 509403.0,
      "text": "in about a day."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 509403.0,
      "end_time": 516680.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 516706.0,
      "end_time": 519701.0,
      "text": "And what you end up with is just the basic chassis of a house"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 519701.0,
      "end_time": 522159.0,
      "text": "onto which you can then apply systems like windows"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 522159.0,
      "end_time": 524217.0,
      "text": "and cladding and insulation and services"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 524217.0,
      "end_time": 527266.0,
      "text": "based on what&#39;s cheap and what&#39;s available."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 527267.0,
      "end_time": 529452.0,
      "text": "Of course, the house is never finished."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 529452.0,
      "end_time": 532333.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re shifting our heads here, so the house is not a finished product."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 532333.0,
      "end_time": 535890.0,
      "text": "With the CNC machine, you can make new parts for it"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 535900.0,
      "end_time": 538947.0,
      "text": "over its life or even use it to make the house next door."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 538947.0,
      "end_time": 542385.0,
      "text": "So we can begin to see the seed of a completely open-source,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 542385.0,
      "end_time": 546660.0,
      "text": "citizen-led urban development model, potentially."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 546660.0,
      "end_time": 550209.0,
      "text": "And we and others have built a few prototypes around the world now,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 550210.0,
      "end_time": 552331.0,
      "text": "and some really interesting lessons here."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 552331.0,
      "end_time": 554658.0,
      "text": "One of them is that it&#39;s always incredibly sociable."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 554658.0,
      "end_time": 559356.0,
      "text": "People get confused between construction work and having fun."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 559356.0,
      "end_time": 562150.0,
      "text": "But the principles of openness go right down"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 562150.0,
      "end_time": 564821.0,
      "text": "into the really mundane, physical details."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 564821.0,
      "end_time": 567824.0,
      "text": "Like, never designing a piece that can&#39;t be lifted up."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 567824.0,
      "end_time": 569122.0,
      "text": "Or, when you&#39;re designing a piece,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 569123.0,
      "end_time": 572300.0,
      "text": "make sure you either can&#39;t put it in the wrong way round,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 572300.0,
      "end_time": 574956.0,
      "text": "or, if you do, it doesn&#39;t matter, because it&#39;s symmetrical."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 574956.0,
      "end_time": 578998.0,
      "text": "Probably the principal which runs deepest with us"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 578998.0,
      "end_time": 581953.0,
      "text": "is the principal set out by Linus Torvalds,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 581953.0,
      "end_time": 584678.0,
      "text": "the open-source pioneer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 584678.0,
      "end_time": 587967.0,
      "text": "which was that idea of, \"Be lazy like a fox.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 587967.0,
      "end_time": 589675.0,
      "text": "Don&#39;t reinvent the wheel every time."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 589676.0,
      "end_time": 593469.0,
      "text": "Take what already works, and adapt it for your own needs."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 593469.0,
      "end_time": 596520.0,
      "text": "Contrary to almost everything that you might get taught"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 596520.0,
      "end_time": 600149.0,
      "text": "at an architecture school, copying is good."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 600149.0,
      "end_time": 602150.0,
      "text": "Which is appropriate, because actually,"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 602150.0,
      "end_time": 603930.0,
      "text": "this approach is not innovative."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 603930.0,
      "end_time": 605539.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s actually how we built buildings"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 605539.0,
      "end_time": 608350.0,
      "text": "for hundreds of years before the Industrial Revolution"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 608350.0,
      "end_time": 610462.0,
      "text": "in these sorts of community barn-raisings."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 610462.0,
      "end_time": 612606.0,
      "text": "The only difference between traditional"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 612606.0,
      "end_time": 615140.0,
      "text": "vernacular architecture and open-source architecture"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 615140.0,
      "end_time": 617134.0,
      "text": "might be a web connection,"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 617134.0,
      "end_time": 619946.0,
      "text": "but it&#39;s a really, really big difference."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 619946.0,
      "end_time": 621377.0,
      "text": "We shared the whole of WikiHouse"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 621377.0,
      "end_time": 623218.0,
      "text": "under a Creative Commons license,"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 623219.0,
      "end_time": 624641.0,
      "text": "and now what&#39;s just beginning to happen"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 624641.0,
      "end_time": 626622.0,
      "text": "is that groups around the world are beginning to take it"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 626623.0,
      "end_time": 629362.0,
      "text": "and use it and hack it and tinker with it, and it&#39;s amazing."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 629362.0,
      "end_time": 632327.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a cool group over in Christchurch in New Zealand"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 632327.0,
      "end_time": 635462.0,
      "text": "looking at post-earthquake development housing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 635462.0,
      "end_time": 638710.0,
      "text": "and thanks to the TED city Prize,"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 638710.0,
      "end_time": 641449.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re working with an awesome group in one of Rio&#39;s favelas"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 641449.0,
      "end_time": 643938.0,
      "text": "to set up a kind of community factory"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 643938.0,
      "end_time": 645852.0,
      "text": "and micro-university."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 645852.0,
      "end_time": 647716.0,
      "text": "These are very, very small beginnings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 647716.0,
      "end_time": 650591.0,
      "text": "and actually there&#39;s more people in the last week"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 650591.0,
      "end_time": 652774.0,
      "text": "who have got in touch and they&#39;re not even on this map."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 652774.0,
      "end_time": 656514.0,
      "text": "I hope next time you see it, you won&#39;t even be able to see the map."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 656514.0,
      "end_time": 660963.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re aware that WikiHouse is a very, very small answer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 660963.0,
      "end_time": 664535.0,
      "text": "but it&#39;s a small answer to a really, really big question,"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 664535.0,
      "end_time": 668310.0,
      "text": "which is that globally, right now, the fastest-growing cities"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 668311.0,
      "end_time": 670542.0,
      "text": "are not skyscraper cities."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 670542.0,
      "end_time": 674638.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re self-made cities in one form or another."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 674638.0,
      "end_time": 678262.0,
      "text": "If we&#39;re talking about the 21st-century city,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 678262.0,
      "end_time": 680886.0,
      "text": "these are the guys who are going to be making it."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 680886.0,
      "end_time": 685367.0,
      "text": "You know, like it or not, welcome to the world&#39;s biggest design team."
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 685368.0,
      "end_time": 687494.0,
      "text": "So if we&#39;re serious about problems"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 687494.0,
      "end_time": 691648.0,
      "text": "like climate change, urbanization and health,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 691648.0,
      "end_time": 695546.0,
      "text": "actually, our existing development models aren&#39;t going to do it."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 695546.0,
      "end_time": 697634.0,
      "text": "As I think Robert Neuwirth said, there isn&#39;t a bank"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 697634.0,
      "end_time": 700411.0,
      "text": "or a corporation or a government or an NGO"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 700411.0,
      "end_time": 701796.0,
      "text": "who&#39;s going to be able to do it"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 701797.0,
      "end_time": 705446.0,
      "text": "if we treat citizens only as consumers."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 705446.0,
      "end_time": 709227.0,
      "text": "How extraordinary would it be, though, if collectively"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 709227.0,
      "end_time": 711500.0,
      "text": "we were to develop solutions not just to the problem"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 711500.0,
      "end_time": 713914.0,
      "text": "of structure that we&#39;ve been working on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 713914.0,
      "end_time": 718634.0,
      "text": "but to infrastructure problems like solar-powered air conditioning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 718634.0,
      "end_time": 721450.0,
      "text": "off-grid energy, off-grid sanitation --"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 721450.0,
      "end_time": 725379.0,
      "text": "low-cost, open-source, high-performance solutions"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 725379.0,
      "end_time": 727319.0,
      "text": "that anyone can very, very easily make,"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 727319.0,
      "end_time": 729219.0,
      "text": "and to put them all into a commons"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 729220.0,
      "end_time": 733568.0,
      "text": "where they&#39;re owned by everyone and they&#39;re accessible by everyone?"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 733568.0,
      "end_time": 737738.0,
      "text": "A kind of Wikipedia for stuff?"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 737738.0,
      "end_time": 739779.0,
      "text": "And once something&#39;s in the commons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 739779.0,
      "end_time": 741135.0,
      "text": "it will always be there."
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 741135.0,
      "end_time": 744663.0,
      "text": "How much would that change the rules?"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 744663.0,
      "end_time": 748990.0,
      "text": "And I think the technology&#39;s on our side."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 748990.0,
      "end_time": 751759.0,
      "text": "If design&#39;s great project in the 20th century"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 751759.0,
      "end_time": 755520.0,
      "text": "was the democratization of consumption --"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 755520.0,
      "end_time": 761946.0,
      "text": "that was Henry Ford, Levittown, Coca-Cola, IKEA —"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 761946.0,
      "end_time": 765568.0,
      "text": "I think design&#39;s great project in the 21st century"
